The health and safety of your children is always our top priority. In addition to taking extensive precautions against illness, we aim to keep parents well-informed of health issues that come to our attention. 

This letter is being sent to inform you that there has recently been a confirmed case of gastroenteritis in Year 1. Although there have been no further official diagnoses, we have become aware of several other Y1 children showing symptoms.

<b style="">School Precautions</b>
To prevent any further spread of illness, we are further requesting that all <b style="">Year 1</b> students stay home from school on Monday (November 27th). This will enable a full disinfection of classroom surfaces. Any other students showing symptoms should also remain at home until they return to full health. 

Additionally, the school will immediately take the following action:
<ul><li>All students will be checked for symptoms, and parents of any unwell students will be contacted to collect their children.</li><li>A full disinfection of Y1 classrooms &amp; Campus common areas (including canteen, bathrooms and kitchen).</li><li>Lower Campus meals prepared offsite on Monday, to enable full deep-cleaning.</li><li>Our usual hygiene routines will be strictly reinforced and monitored.</li></ul>Please note that the school has recently been fully inspected and approved by the Ministry of Health, as part of routine procedures. We are confident that our usual robust precautions combined with these additional actions, will prevent any further spread of illness.

<b style="">General Information from the UK National Health Service</b>

