"Gastroenteritis is a very common condition that causes diarrhoea and vomiting. Itâ€™s usually caused by a bacterial or viral tummy bug. It effects people of all ages, but is particularly common in young children."

Symptoms:
"The main symptoms gastroenteritis are sudden, watery diarrhoea; feeling sick; vomiting; and mild fever. Some people also have other symptoms, such as loss of appetite, an upset stomach and headaches. The symptoms usually appear after a day after becoming infected. They typically last less than a week, but can sometimes last longer."

